## ðŸ”µ Module 3: The Cloud (Remotes)

### 8. Linking to GitHub
**Command:** `git remote add origin <URL>`
*   **What:** Saves a URL with a nickname (standard name is `origin`).
*   **Why:** So you don't have to type the full HTTPS link every time.

**Command:** `git push -u origin main`
*   **What:** Uploads your commits to the server.
*   **Why:** To backup your code and share it.
*   **`-u`**: Stands for "Upstream". It links your local folder to the cloud folder permanently, so next time you can just type `git push`.

### 9. Downloading Code
**Command:** `git clone <URL>`
*   **What:** Downloads an entire repository from the web to a new folder.
*   **Why:** To get a copy of a project to start working on it (simulating a second computer/developer).

**Command:** `git pull`
*   **What:** Downloads changes from the cloud *and* merges them into your file.
*   **Why:** To update your local code with what your teammates have done.

